profile_description:Yunnan Pu'er Catimor Natural 1650m\vMoisture: 11.5% | Density: 759g/L\vSuggested load: 60g\v\vVersion 2 - Based on V1 first roast data (log0077)\v\vV1 findings:\v- Weight loss only 8% (underdeveloped)\v- Mid-section tracked 5-7C below profile (preheat too low)\v- FC signal very weak, estimated ~194C\v- ROR stayed positive throughout (excellent curve shape)\v- Floral aroma present but flavor thin\v- Two extractions confirmed: issue is roast development, not brewing\v\vV2 changes from V1:\v1. Preheat: 720W -> 770W (+50W to fix mid-section lag)\v2. expect_fc: 200 -> 197C (based on actual FC ~194C)\v3. Mid-section: 10s faster, 2C higher to reduce profile lag\v4. Endpoint: 350s/200C -> 370s/204C (+20s, +4C for development)\v5. roast_levels: 196-208 -> 198-210C (shift +2C)\v\vRecommended Levels:\v  Nordic Light: Level 1.0 (~198C, ~10-12% dev)\v  Light Filter: Level 1.5 (~200C, ~13-15% dev)\v  Sweet & Balanced: Level 2.0 (~202C, ~16-18% dev)\v  Full Development: Level 2.5 (~204C, ~19-21% dev)\v\vTarget: Level 2.0 (202C)\vExpected weight loss: 10-12%\vExpected dev ratio: 14-17%\v\vSafety: No zone boosts, standard end_ratio/min_ROR.\v
